locality: South Africa, Northern Cape, Kamieskroon, Theuns se dam. Perennial dwarf shrub, 1 m high. Leaves opposite, simple, succulent, whitish-green, margins entire. solitary flowers, white tinged with pink. Succulent karoo with Zygophyllum, Fragonia, Lycium, Arctotheca, Dimorphotheca, Leyssera and Aridaria. On mountain slope, very gentle N slope of < 15ยบ, soil well-drained granite sand, full sun. In pasture, common, native.
Augrabies Waterfall National Park. New part of park, close to picnic spot (Af en Toe). Grid ref. 2819DB.
